---
// ValueAnchor.astro — Section 4 (light)
// The claims-safe "one saved job" framing, styled as a technical-drawing
// dimension line (two labelled measurement ticks joined by a dashed run) —
// a genuine use of the blueprint measurement-tick motif, not decoration.
// Deliberately carries no dollar figures for job value (none exist in
// site.ts) — the comparison stays qualitative, and the note ties back to
// the disclaimer's "results depend on" framing.
---

<section class="va band-light section">
  <div class="container va__inner">
    <div class="va__copy">
      <p class="mono-label va__cap">The measurement that matters</p>
      <h2 class="va__title">One saved job can cover a lot of this.</h2>
      <p class="va__body max-measure">
        A missed call on a roof at 2pm. A quote that goes quiet. A
        switchboard job that goes to the next tradie because nobody replied
        in time. On their own, moments like these can be worth more than a
        month of running this system. One booked job you would otherwise
        have lost can go a long way toward covering the investment — that's
        the maths worth doing before comparing this to software pricing.
      </p>
      <p class="va__note">
        Illustrative framing, not a promise. Results depend on your market,
        pricing, availability, and how quickly you respond.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="va__ruler" aria-hidden="true">
      <span class="va__tick">
        <span class="va__tick-mark"></span>
        <span class="mono-label va__tick-label">One job lost</span>
      </span>
      <span class="va__line"></span>
      <span class="va__tick va__tick--end">
        <span class="va__tick-mark"></span>
        <span class="mono-label va__tick-label">One month, managed</span>
      </span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .va__inner {
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
  }

  .va__cap {
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
  }
  .va__title {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    max-width: 20ch;
  }
  .va__body {
    color: var(--body);
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
  }
  .va__note {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  /* Dimension-line ruler — two ticks, one dashed run between them. */
  .va__ruler {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0;
    padding-block: 0.5rem;
  }
  .va__tick {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .va__tick--end {
    align-items: flex-end;
  }
  .va__tick-mark {
    width: 1.5px;
    height: 28px;
    background: var(--ink);
  }
  .va__tick-label {
    color: var(--muted);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .va__line {
    flex: 1;
    height: 1px;
    margin-inline: 0.75rem;
    background: repeating-linear-gradient(
      to right,
      var(--line-light) 0,
      var(--line-light) 6px,
      transparent 6px,
      transparent 12px
    );
    align-self: center;
    margin-bottom: 1.6rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .va__ruler {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: stretch;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }
    .va__tick,
    .va__tick--end {
      flex-direction: row;
      align-items: center;
    }
    .va__tick-mark {
      width: 28px;
      height: 1.5px;
    }
    .va__line {
      width: 1px;
      height: 32px;
      margin: 0 0 0 13px;
      background: repeating-linear-gradient(
        to bottom,
        var(--line-light) 0,
        var(--line-light) 6px,
        transparent 6px,
        transparent 12px
      );
    }
  }
</style>
